tinfour.las

Class GeoTiffData

  • java.lang.Object
    • tinfour.las.GeoTiffData

  • public class GeoTiffData
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides the main data collection for accessing data from the embedded GeoTIFF tags in a LAS file.

    • Method Detail

      • containsKey

        public boolean containsKey(int keyCode)
        Indicates whether the GeoTiffData collection contains an entry for the specified key code. This method does not indicate whether the specified code is a valid value, only whether it is available in the data set.
        Parameters:
        keyCode - an integer key code
        Returns:
        true if the collection includes an entry for the code, otherwise false.

      • getInteger

        public int getInteger(int keyCode)
               throws java.io.IOException
        Gets the single integer value associated with the GeoTIFF keycode.
        Parameters:
        keyCode - a valid GeoTIFF key
        Returns:
        a positive integer value in the range 0 to 65535 (the range of an unsigned short integer)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - in the event of a TIFF format exception or the key code is not found.

      • getDouble

        public double[] getDouble(int keyCode)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Gets an array of one or more doubles containing the value or values associated with the specified key code.
        Parameters:
        keyCode - a valid GeoTIFF key
        Returns:
        a valid array
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - in the event of a TIFF format exception
